== README

Create a local website utilizing the ruby gem â€œtimezone" that allows you to input a country and a state/province/territory/region via a form.


-The title of the project is called WorldTime 

-Each country and state should be saved to a database

-On the home page you should display all countries found in the database. 

-Each country displayed should show its current date and time 

-Link each country to its wikipedia article

-If state/province/territory/region exists link this to wikipedia too.

-An icon should indicate if a country observes Daylight Savings Time

-Make things look nice using twitter bootstrap as your css style.

Gems: Bootstrap, Devise, Timezone, Geokit
